Test 2 — Linear Motion Validation  (v7 — M5 FIXED)
====================================================

ONLY CHANGES FROM v7
---------------------
1. LiDAR x correction added to _imu_tick()
   — records wall distance at origin (S1)
   — every tick during S2 and S4: true_x = (wall_origin - wall_now) / 1000
   — feeds true_x into EKF so position stays anchored to reality
   — this fixes M5: robot IS at origin, now EKF agrees

2. update_lidar_x() added to EKF class
   — single observation H=[1,0,0,0,0], R=0.01 (trust LiDAR strongly)

EVERYTHING ELSE IDENTICAL TO v7
---------------------------------
  PWM_SPEED       = 50
  RIGHT_BOOST     = 8  (forward) 
  RIGHT_BOOST_BWD = 6.5   (backward)
  LIDAR_FORWARD_ANGLE = 180
  STILL_BETWEEN_S = 5.0
  Motor pin logic, IMU, EKF, StationaryDetector — all unchanged

Usage:
  python3 test2_v7_fixed.py
  python3 test2_v7_fixed.py --boost 15
  python3 test2_v7_fixed.py --boost-bwd 9
"""

